00:10:47.040 --> 00:10:53.180
It's because there is one other
rule to be aware of in WCAG,

00:10:53.180 --> 00:10:56.610
and that is contrast of large text.

00:10:56.610 --> 00:10:59.780
So if you do have text that's
a certain size or larger,

00:10:59.780 --> 00:11:01.900
the requirement goes down.

00:11:01.900 --> 00:11:06.270
It goes down from 4.5-to-1
contrast down to three to one.

00:11:06.270 --> 00:11:07.930
So it’s bigger on screen.

00:11:07.930 --> 00:11:08.950
You just have more of it to read.

00:11:08.950 --> 00:11:12.180
It doesn't need as much
contrast to be perceivable.

00:11:12.180 --> 00:11:17.490
So the requirement for that 3-to-1,
that starts at 18-point text.

00:11:17.490 --> 00:11:20.820
Now in pixels, on the web,
that's going to be 24 pixels.

00:11:20.820 --> 00:11:26.230
If that text is bold, 14 point
or 18 and two-thirds pixels.

00:11:26.230 --> 00:11:28.410
That's that 3-to-1
contrast requirement.

00:11:32.300 --> 00:11:35.120
That’s why using
this tool in WAVE...

00:11:35.120 --> 00:11:37.540
