00:22:39.560 --> 00:22:42.180
There was a question about
adding an ARIA label.

00:22:42.180 --> 00:22:44.530
And I'm going to lump
that all into one category

00:22:44.530 --> 00:22:48.250
of making this accessible
for screen readers.

00:22:48.250 --> 00:22:53.580
And this is not about a blind
users or screen-reader users;

00:22:53.580 --> 00:22:56.150
this is about sighted users.

00:22:56.150 --> 00:22:58.550
So the thing with the
ARIA label is that

00:22:58.550 --> 00:23:01.240
and maybe some other
techniques might help me

00:23:01.240 --> 00:23:03.050
if I'm using a screen reader.

00:23:03.050 --> 00:23:05.039
But a screen reader is
actually already going

00:23:05.040 --> 00:23:06.120
to tell me it's a label.

00:23:06.120 --> 00:23:08.270
So this is purely a visual thing.

00:23:08.270 --> 00:23:11.040
This is really just about
differentiating colors.

00:23:11.040 --> 00:23:13.390
And so the ARIA in this case,
you're not going to be able

00:23:13.390 --> 00:23:16.130
to add anything with ARIA
labels or anything else

00:23:16.131 --> 00:23:17.500
that would address this.

00:23:17.500 --> 00:23:19.650
It would really have to be at the
level of the colors you choose.

00:23:21.310 --> 00:23:23.760
Another question from Megan;
a really good question.

00:23:23.760 --> 00:23:28.310
And that is if there's different
requirements, the link is standalone.

00:23:28.310 --> 00:23:33.500
So you gave the example, Megan, in
your question, maybe of navigation.

00:23:33.500 --> 00:23:36.200
So on this page with the
