00:23:40.350 --> 00:23:43.970
on the WebAIM site,
and they are not underlined,

00:23:43.970 --> 00:23:49.380
because they are clearly
presented as links.

00:23:49.380 --> 00:23:51.960
Again, this is about
the visual presentation.

00:23:51.960 --> 00:23:57.790
And if I can not perceive color, I am
still going to know those are links.

00:23:57.790 --> 00:24:04.130
Regardless of the color perception
or contrast sensitivity,

00:24:04.130 --> 00:24:05.760
I'm still going to be able to tell.

00:24:05.760 --> 00:24:07.510
So, yes, good question.

00:24:07.510 --> 00:24:10.340
That would not need
to be underlined.

00:24:10.340 --> 00:24:12.300
Or if there's other styling.

00:24:12.300 --> 00:24:14.820
Sometimes you got links
that look like buttons.

00:24:14.820 --> 00:24:17.600
They are links under the hood, and
you've made them look like buttons,

00:24:17.600 --> 00:24:19.420
and you no longer
have those underlined.

00:24:19.420 --> 00:24:20.910
That's another example
in the question.

00:24:20.910 --> 00:24:22.090
That's fine too.

00:24:22.090 --> 00:24:26.020
Really, this is about just not
relying on color as the only way

00:24:26.020 --> 00:24:27.020
to present that.

