00:25:35.570 --> 00:25:36.720
how's that possible?

00:25:36.720 --> 00:25:40.440
Well, the reason that's possible
is because numbers five to 15,

00:25:40.440 --> 00:25:43.170
most of them kind of fall
into the same category.

00:25:43.170 --> 00:25:45.360
And that is,
you got to interact with the thing.

00:25:46.570 --> 00:25:52.040
There are only a few things that
you can detect just at a glance

00:25:52.040 --> 00:25:53.600
or using tools like WAVE.

00:25:53.600 --> 00:25:56.550
A lot of it has to do with
the interaction that happens,

00:25:56.550 --> 00:25:59.777
because you need to consider
the contrast of things

00:25:59.778 --> 00:26:01.080
in different states.

00:26:01.080 --> 00:26:03.690
So if I have this custom
checkbox and I hover over it,

00:26:03.690 --> 00:26:08.020
and so it changes from gray to
blue... Or if I have a link,

00:26:08.020 --> 00:26:11.570
and when I hover over that link,
it gets lighter, as an example,

00:26:12.690 --> 00:26:16.710
now those are different states
where the contrast has changed,

00:26:16.710 --> 00:26:18.330
and I'm going to need to test that.

00:26:18.330 --> 00:26:20.370
So that's a lot of these.

00:26:20.370 --> 00:26:22.890
Five, six, seven, eight,
they are all different states

00:26:22.890 --> 00:26:24.450
of that checkbox border.

00:26:24.450 --> 00:26:26.800
Hover, focus, active, checked.

00:26:26.800 --> 00:26:29.780
Now some of these are
just super fast tests.

00:26:29.780 --> 00:26:33.090
If I'm hovering with my mouse
and something does not change,

00:26:33.090 --> 00:26:38.770
or it gets darker, well, I don't
need to dig deeper with that.

00:26:38.770 --> 00:26:40.800
I don't need to pull out
other tools or techniques.

00:26:41.960 --> 00:26:45.580
If it has enough contrast and it
gets darker on the background,

00:26:45.580 --> 00:26:47.990
it's going to have more contrast.

00:26:47.990 --> 00:26:51.220
So some of these are like one-second
checks, but it's important

00:26:51.220 --> 00:26:51.890
to do this.

00:26:51.890 --> 00:26:57.070
When I interact with this thing, when
I check it, when I follow a link,

00:26:57.070 --> 00:27:00.510
does it... You don't have as
many sites with this anymore,

00:27:00.510 --> 00:27:04.880
but if it has, like...
Sorry, transitioning to the links.

00:27:04.880 --> 00:27:08.290
Does it have, like,
a visited state, you know?

00:27:08.290 --> 00:27:10.510
It’s hover, focus, active, visited.

00:27:10.510 --> 00:27:11.750
So that's a bunch of these.

00:27:11.750 --> 00:27:15.187
Nine, ten, eleven,
twelve; hover, focus, active,

00:27:15.188 --> 00:27:16.940
and visited for my link.

