00:32:03.970 --> 00:32:07.500
between the hover and focus states...
So you've got gray default,

00:32:07.500 --> 00:32:11.580
blue hover, and then just this
light gray little glow on focus...

00:32:11.580 --> 00:32:17.140
It actually passes all of the
requirements in WCAG at levels A

00:32:17.140 --> 00:32:21.330
and double A, up to version 2.1,
which is the current version.

00:32:21.330 --> 00:32:24.290
There's kind of this weird
gap where in the contrast one,

00:32:24.290 --> 00:32:27.690
it says, well, you need at least
3-to-1 contrast for every state,

00:32:27.690 --> 00:32:30.860
but not differences between states.

00:32:30.860 --> 00:32:35.090
And in the color one, it says
you can’t rely on color alone,

00:32:35.090 --> 00:32:37.400
but it does not have
a minimum contrast.

00:32:37.400 --> 00:32:41.150
So there's this weird little gap
where this little subtle glow,

00:32:41.150 --> 00:32:44.160
even though it's very light and
has less than 3-to-1 contrast,

00:32:44.160 --> 00:32:47.490
would not fail anything
in version 2.1.

00:32:47.490 --> 00:32:49.560
So there is a version 2.2.

00:32:50.700 --> 00:32:53.360
